Definicin

Un Diagrama de caja, tambin conocido como diagrama de caja y bigotes, es un grfico que est basado en cuartiles y mediante el cual se visualiza la distribucin de un conjunto de datos. Est compuesto por un rectngulo, la "caja", y dos brazos, los "bigotes".

Qu podemos aprender?

Podemos aprender el valor mnimo, el mximo, los cuartiles Q1, Q2 y Q3 y el rango inter-cuartlico (RIC):

Tutorial

Nos ayuda a comparar distribuciones

Comparacin entre grficos

A box plot consists of a box and whiskers. The box goes from the 25th percentile to the 75th percentile of the data, also known as the inter-quartile range (IQR). The whiskers start from the edge of the box and extend to the furthest data point that is within 1.5 times the IQR.

Comparacin entre grficos.

Grfico de caja bsico

ggplot(ToothGrowth, aes(x=supp, y=len)) + geom_boxplot()

Cambiar el ancho del grfico

Cambia el ancho con width

ggplot(ToothGrowth, aes(x=supp, y=len)) + geom_boxplot(width=0.1)

Los outliers estn representados como puntos

Agregar muescas al plot

ggplot(ToothGrowth, aes(x=supp, y=len)) +  geom_boxplot(notch=TRUE)

Hacer un grfico violn

Violin plots are a way of comparing multiple data distributions. With ordinary density curves, it is difficult to compare more than just a few distributions because the lines visually interfere with each other. With a violin plot, its easier to compare several dis tributions since theyre placed side by side.

ggplot(ToothGrowth, aes(x=supp, y=len)) +  geom_violin()

Grfico violn

p<-ggplot(ToothGrowth, aes(x=supp, y=len)) +  geom_violin()
p + geom_violin() + geom_boxplot(width=.1, fill="black") + stat_summary(fun.y=median, geom="point", fill="white", shape=21, size=2.5)
